The exotic sharks have been bred at the Atlantis Submarine Voyage but they needed the special nursery as they are still too small to be moved to the main display.

Currently they are only seven inches long but they will grow to over one metre when they reach maturity.

They will then be moved to the Atlantis Submarine Voyage, where visitors can ride through the tank and see scores of sharks up close.

Aquarium curator Iain Grieve said: 'We are delighted to have successfully hatched so many babies this year.

'They are far too small to go into the main display, where guests are submerged in yellow submarines with giant underwater viewing windows.

'So we have created a special nursery for them to grow up in which offers an amazing 360-degree view.'

